ew Zealand) is a New Zealand Professional boxer of Samoan heritage, is a two time New Zealand Middleweight Champion, a former UBF Asia Pacific Middleweight Champion, [[King in the Ring#The Force|The Force]] Super Middleweight Champion and the current [[World Boxing Council|WBC]] - [[Oriental and Pacific Boxing Federation|OPBF]] Super Middleweight champion and [[World Boxing Association|WBA]] Oceania Super Middleweight champion. He has defeated many credible boxers including [[Gunnar Jackson]], [[Adrian Taihia]], [[Jordan Tai]], and more. Auimatagi trains out of Papatoetoe Boxing Club with Grant Arkell as his trainer and manager. Grant Arkell trained Joseph Parker during his amateur fights.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/sport/news/article.cfm?c_id=4&objectid=11666410 |title=The story behind the gym that found Joseph Parker|publisher=Stuff |date= 2016-06-30|accessdate=2019-06-16}}</ref> One of Auimatagi's biggest win of his career was against Morgan Jones. In the last round of that bout, Mose got knocked down early in the round, however he returned and TKO his opponent with only 8 seconds left in the fight. Mose comes from a long line of Professional boxers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/combat-sports/102747859/mose-auimatagi-jnr-scores-sensational-last-minute-ko-win-on-joseph-parker-undercard |title=Mose Auimatagi Jnr scores sensational last minute TKO win on Joseph Parker undercard|publisher=Stuff |date= 2018-04-01|accessdate=2019-06-16}}</ref>\n\n==Professional titles==\n* New Zealand National Boxing Federation\n** New Zealand National Middleweight title (158\u00bc ''Ibs'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/other-sports/81200240/premier-kiwi-boxing-returning-to-freetoair-television |title=Kiwi boxing returns to free-to-air television|publisher=Stuff |date= 2016-06-17|accessdate=2019-06-16}}</ref>\n* [[New Zealand Professional Boxing Association]]\n** New Zealand National Middleweight title (159\u00be ''Ibs'')<ref>{{