{"title_page": "Bleached", "text_new": "{{Short description|American pop band consisting of sisters Jennifer and Jessica Clavin, formerly of Mika Miko}}\n{{Other uses|Bleach (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Bleached\n| image            = Bleached performing at The Great Escape, May 2016.jpg\n| image_size       = 250px\n| image_upright    = \n| landscape        = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = Bleached performing at The Great Escape in May 2016.\n| background       = group_or_band\n| alias            = \n| origin           = Los Angeles, California, United States\n| genre            = {{Flatlist|\n* [[Punk rock]]\n* [[Pop music|pop]] \n* [[rock and roll]]\n* [[garage rock]]\n* [[indie rock]]\n* [[noise pop]]\n* [[garage punk (fusion genre)|garage punk]]\n}}\n| years_active     = {{start date|2011}}\u2013present\n| label            = {{Flatlist|\n* [[Dead Oceans]]\n* [[Suicide Squeeze Records|Suicide Squeeze]]\n}}\n| associated_acts  = {{Flatlist|\n* [[Mika Miko]]\n* Cold Showers\n* [[Cold Cave]]\n* Dead Banana Ladies\n}}\n| website          = {{URL|hellobleached.com}}\n| current_members  = Jennifer Clavin<br>Jessica Clavin<br>Spencer Lere\n| past_members     = Micayla Grace<br>Nick Pillot\n}}\n\n'''Bleached''' is an American [[Pop music|pop]] band consisting of sisters Jennifer and Jessica Clavin, formerly of [[Mika Miko]]. The band plays a style of rock, pop, [[rock and roll]], and [[indie rock]]. Bleached was established in Los Angeles in 2011. The group has released three [[studio album]]s, ''[[Ride Your Heart]]'' (2013), ''[[Welcome the Worms]]'' (2016) and ''[[Don't You Think You've Had Enough?]]'', all with [[Dead Oceans]], and have charted on the [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] charts.\n\n== History ==\n\n[[File:Bleached at Tufnell Park Dome, October 2013.jpg|thumb|left|Bleached performing in London in 2013]]\nThey formed in [[Echo Park, Los Angeles|Echo Park]], [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] during 2011, with [[Mika Miko]] front woman Jennifer Clavin and guitarist Jessica Clavin. Micayla Grace joined in 2014 as a live member and drummer Nick Pillot in 2016.<ref name=\"AllMusic Biography\">{{cite web |first=Heather |last=Phares |title=Bleached : Biography |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/bleached-mn0002766601/biography |publisher=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Los Angeles Times\">{{cite web |first=Todd |last=Martens |title=Echo Park punk band Bleached embraces life's darkness, with an almost beachy exuberance  |url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/la-ca-ms-bleached-20160403-1-story.html |journal=[[Los Angeles Times]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016 |date=April 1, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"The Guardian\">{{cite web |first=Paul |last=Lester |title=Bleached (No 1,261) |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/may/01/new-band-bleached |journal=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016 |date=May 1, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Interview Magazine\">{{cite web |first=Emily |last=McDermott |title=Bleached to the Bone |url=http://www.interviewmagazine.com/music/bleached-welcome-the-worms/ |journal=[[Interview (magazine)|Interview]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016 |date=April 4, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Spin Magazine\">{{cite web |first=Rachel |last=Brodsky |title=Bleached Ditch the Surfboards on \u2018Super-Confident\u2019 New Album |url=http://www.spin.com/2015/12/bleached-new-album-interview/ |journal=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016 |date=December 16, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Consequence of Sound\">{{cite web |first=Alex |last=Young |title=Interview: Jennifer and Jessica Clavin (of Bleached) |url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2012/03/interview-jennifer-and-jessica-clavin-of-bleached/ |publisher=[[Consequence of Sound]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016 |date=March 12, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Bare Magazine\">{{cite web |first=Jamie |last=Santiago |title=Interview with Jessica Clavin of Bleached |url=http://www.baremagazine.org/interview-with-jessica-clavin-of-bleached |journal=[[Bare (magazine)|Bare]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016 |date=June 2, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Anthem Magazine\">{{cite web |first=Cooper |last=Saver |title=Q&A with Bleached |url=http://anthemmagazine.com/qa-with-bleached/ |journal=Anthem |accessdate=April 10, 2016 |date=March 19, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Bloginity\">{{cite web |first=Emmett |last=Lindner |title=Interview: Talking With Jessica Clavin of Bleached |url=http://www.bloginity.com/2011/12/jessica-clavin-interview/ |publisher=[[Bloginity]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016 |date=December 1, 2011}}</ref>\n\nThe band released three [[extended play]]s, ''Francis'', ''Carter'', and ''Searching Through the Past b/w Electric Chair'', soon after their formation. Their subsequent release, a [[studio album]], ''Ride Your Heart'', was released on April 2, 2013,<ref name=\"AllMusic Review One\">{{cite web |first=Heather |last=Phares |title=''Ride Your Heart'' \u2013 Bleached : Review |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/ride-your-heart-mw0002477867 |publisher=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016 |date=April 2, 2013}}</ref> by [[Dead Oceans]].<ref name=\"Metacritic First\">{{cite web |author=[[CBS Interactive]] |title=Critic reviews for Ride Your Heart by Bleached |url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/ride-your-heart/bleached/critic-reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016}}</ref> This album charted on the [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'' magazine]] [[Top Heatseekers|Heatseekers Albums]] chart, where it peaked at No. 18.<ref name=\"AllMusic Awards\">{{cite web |author=[[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] |title=Bleached : Awards |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/bleached-mn0002766601/awards |publisher=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016}}</ref> They released, an extended play, ''For the Feel'', in 2014, from Dead Oceans. The group released another [[studio album]], ''Welcome the Worms'', on April 1, 2016,<ref name=\"AllMusic Review Two\">{{cite web |first=Heather |last=Phares |title=''Welcome the Worms'' \u2013 Bleached : Review |url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/welcome-the-worms-mw0002911783 |publisher=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016 |date=April 1, 2016}}</ref> with Dead Oceans.<ref name=\"Metacritic Second\">{{cite web |author=[[CBS Interactive]] |title=Critic reviews for Welcome the Worms by Bleached |url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/welcome-the-worms/bleached/critic-reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016}}</ref> The album peaked on the Heatseekers Albums chart at No. 15,<ref name=\"Heatseekers Albums\">{{cite web|author=''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''|title=Bleached - Chart history (Top Heatseekers Albums)|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/1557231/bleached/chart?f=324 |accessdate=April 13, 2016}}</ref> while it placed on the [[Independent Albums]] chart at No. 46.<ref name=\"Independent Albums\">{{cite web|author=''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''|title=Bleached - Chart history (Independent Albums)|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/1557231/bleached/chart?f=326 |accessdate=April 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Members ==\n\n[[File:Jennifer Clavin of Bleached at The Great Escape, May 2016 (2).jpg|thumb|right|Jennifer Clavin performing with the band in May 2016]]\n*'''Jennifer Clavin''' \u2013 lead vocals, guitar, synth\n*'''Jessica Clavin''' \u2013 lead guitar, bass\n*'''Nick Pillot''' \u2013 drums, percussion\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Studio albums ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of studio albums, with selected chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\" | Peak chart positions<ref name=\"AllMusic Awards\"/>\n|-\n!style=\"width:3em; font-size:90%\"|[[Top Heatseekers|US<br>Heat]]<ref name=\"Heatseekers Albums\"/>\n!