ative rock groups from California]]\n[[Category:Garage rock groups from California]]\n[[Category:Post-punk revival music groups]]\n[[Category:Sibling musical groups]]\n[[Category:Rock music groups from California]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|American pop band consisting of sisters Jennifer and Jessica Clavin, formerly of Mika Miko}}\n{{Other uses|Bleach (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Bleached\n| image            = Bleached performing at The Great Escape, May 2016.jpg\n| image_size       = 250px\n| image_upright    = \n| landscape        = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = Bleached performing at The Great Escape in May 2016.\n| background       = group_or_band\n| alias            = \n| origin           = Los Angeles, California, United States\n| genre            = {{Flatlist|\n* [[Punk rock]]\n* [[Pop music|pop]] \n* [[rock and roll]]\n* [[garage rock]]\n* [[indie rock]]\n* [[noise pop]]\n* [[garage punk (fusion genre)|garage punk]]\n}}\n| years_active     = {{start date|2011}}\u2013present\n| label            = {{Flatlist|\n* [[Dead Oceans]]\n* [[Suicide Squeeze Records|Suicide Squeeze]]\n}}\n| associated_acts  = {{Flatlist|\n* [[Mika Miko]]\n* Cold Showers\n* [[Cold Cave]]\n* Dead Banana Ladies\n}}\n| website          = {{URL|hellobleached.com}}\n| current_members  = Jennifer Clavin<br>Jessica Clavin<br>Spencer Lere\n| past_members     = Micayla Grace<br>Nick Pillot\n}}\n\n'''Bleached''' is an American [[Pop music|pop]] band consisting of sisters Jennifer and Jessica Clavin, formerly of [[Mika Miko]]. The band plays a style of rock, pop, [[rock and roll]], and [[indie rock]]. Bleached was established in Los Angeles in 2011. The group has released three [[studio album]]s, ''[[Ride Your Heart]]'' (2013), ''[[Welcome the Worms]]'' (2016) and ''[[Don't You Think You've Had Enough?]]'', all with [[Dead Oceans]], and have charted on the [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] charts.\n\n== History ==\n\n[[File:Bleached at Tufnell Park Dome, October 2013.jpg|thumb|left|Bleached performing in London in 2013]]\nThey formed in [[Echo Park, Los Angeles|Echo Park]], [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] during 2011, with [[Mika Miko]] front woman Jennifer Clavin and guitarist Jessica Clavin. Micayla Grace joined in 2014 as a live member and drummer Nick Pillot in 2016.<ref name=\"AllMusic Biography\">{{cite web |first=Heather |last=Phares |title=Bleached : Biography |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/bleached-mn0002766601/biography |publisher=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Los Angeles Times\">{{cite web |first=Todd |last=Martens |title=Echo Park punk band Bleached embraces life's darkness, with an almost beachy exuberance  |url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/la-ca-ms-bleached-20160403-1-story.html |journal=[[Los Angeles Times]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016 |date=April 1, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"The Guardian\">{{cite web |first=Paul |last=Lester |title=Bleached (No 1,261) |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/may/01/new-band-bleached |journal=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016 |date=May 1, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"Interview Magazine\">{{cite web |first=Emily |last=McDermott |title=Bleached to the Bone |url=http://www.interviewmagazine.com/music/bleached-welcome-the-worms/ |journal=[[Interview (magazine)|Interview]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016 |date=April 4, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Spin Magazine\">{{cite web |first=Rachel |last=Brodsky |title=Bleached Ditch the Surfboards on \u2018Super-Confident\u2019 New Album |url=http://www.spin.com/2015/12/bleached-new-album-interview/ |journal=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] |accessdate=April 10, 2016 |date=December 16, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Consequence of Sound\">{{cite web |first=Alex |last=Young |title=Interview: Jennifer and Jessica Clavin (of Bleached) |url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2012/03/interview-jennifer-and-jessica-clavin-of-bleached/ |publisher=[[Consequence of Sound]] |accessdate=April 1